Description: Three head studies, on white ground: from right to left, young prince with turban, his old uncle, and his page carrying a spear on his shoulder; all in profile to left; illustration to Denon's 'Voyage dans la Basse et la Haute Egypte' (Paris, 1802), volume II, plate 106. c.1799/1802 Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Baron Dominique Vivant Denon
Curator's comments: Engraved for Denon's 'Voyage dans la Basse et la Haute Egypte', see 1952,0405.104.
